						<h2>Keep users watching</h2>
						<div class="line"></div>
					</div>
					<div class="context-info">
						<h3>Ideating and Presenting Design</h3>
						<p>
						Another key challenge was how to keep users using the video player longer&mdash;even if they didn't know what to watch. 
						</br></br>
						From our initial research&mdash;reports and articles found online&mdash;we learned that our main demographic enjoyed the constant background noise and low-barrier-to-entry cable T.V. experiences provided&mdash;just turn it on, and go from there. </br></br>
						Before any detail design, I wanted to validate how users might navigate through the video content and how that could meet our business objectives. Focusing on our goals to keep users entertained while reducing the cost to finding the right content, I <em>sketched</em> and <em>wireframed</em> user flow iterations for our prioritized scenarios.
						</br></br>
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
